Rating: 4
I put the cake in the oven sans parchment paper and THEN read the reviews about how difficult it is to remove from the pan. But mine still came out intact! Tips for removal: 1 - As soon as cake is out of oven, run a dull knife around the edge of pan to loosen. 2 - After the cake has cooled for 10-15 minutes, stand the cake pan up on a 45 degree angle, and firmly tap the pan against the kitchen counter (lay a towel down to protect your counter surface); rotate it like a wheel, and tap again. This helps loosen the cake from the bottom before you turn it out of the pan.

