I am fortunate enough to have raspberries in our yard, thanks to my unsuccessful attempts at pruning my husband's garden. This recipe is an ideal way to use them: the combination of sweet & tart is perfect, and whether for dessert or breakfast, it's irresistible. I follow the recipe exactly and use Cabot's unsalted butter - beating for 2 minutes is important - and bake for 20 minutes. Even though it's quite moist, the cake comes right out of the pan. No need for accompaniment, either.

